  2    The area in front of Barracks is for unloading only  Unload all of your cadet s baggage where directed  The driver must stay with the vehicle   Airport style drop off  3    Immediately after your vehicle is unloaded  proceed through the semi circle and continue back to the Parade Ground parking area  4    Park the vehicle and rejoin your cadet  Lunch Lunch will be provided for the new cadets from 11 00 a m    1 30 p m  in Crozet Hall  New cadets can eat at no charge  the cost for family members for lunch is 9 00  includes tax  for adults and children  children 5 and under eat free It is important that new cadets eat during this time and to drink plenty of fluids with the meal  Dress Be sure to wear casual clothing and good walking shoes  The weather in August tends to be hot and humid and we want you to be as comfortable as possible General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Matriculation Day Brochure Katrina Butner Office Manager P   540  464 7104 F   540  464 7660 Email the Office 201 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  2445  General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Matriculation Day Brochure Katrina Butner Office Manager P   540  464 7104 F   540  464 7660 Email the Office 201 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  2445 General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions General Information General Information Events Events Directions Directions Directions What you need to bring What you need to bring Matriculation Details Matriculation Details Especially for parents Especially for parents New Cadet Oath Ceremony New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Frequently Asked Questions Ma