here to stop your vehicle to unload  2    The area in front of Barracks is for unloading only  Unload all of your cadet s baggage where directed  The driver must stay with the vehicle   Airport style drop off  3    Immediately after your vehicle is unloaded  proceed through the semi circle and continue back to the Parade Ground parking area  4    Park the vehicle and rejoin your cadet  Lunch Lunch will be provided for the new cadets from 11 00 a m    1 30 p m  in Crozet Hall  New cadets can eat at no charge  the cost for family members for lunch is 9 00  includes tax  for adults and children  children 5 and under eat free It is important that new cadets eat during this time and to drink plenty of fluids with the meal  Dress Be sure to wear casual clothing and good walking shoes  The weather in August tends to be hot and humid and we want you to be as comfortable as possible      Getting here  getting around  getting fed Driving Directions Parking The first event of the day is in Cameron Hall  which is about a five minute walk from the Parade Ground  Signs will direct you how to park on the Parade Ground weather permitting  Shuttle service to Cameron Hall will be available from Moody Hall  Weather permitting Parade Ground parking will be available beginning at 6 15 a m  Vehicle entry onto the Parade Ground will be in front of Marshall Museum    Shuttle services will be provided from VMI Post locations to Cameron Hall from 7 a m  until 4 p m  In the event that the Parade Ground is closed for parking due to inclement weather  shuttle services will be provided from the Lowe s parking lot    An information table with brochures will be set up in front of Preston Library  Unloading Baggage Please use extreme caution during this period  You must unload baggage by 1 30 p m  Please note that room assignments will be provided at matriculation processing in Cameron Hall  Due to congestion in front of Barracks  we suggest that new cadets carry their luggage to Barracks from the 